        <p data-aos="fade-up">
Visual Paradigm is a software application designed for software development teams to model business information systems and manage development processes. In addition to modeling support, this technology provides report generation and code engineering capabilities including code generation.
        </p>
             <h1 data-aos="fade-up" style="color:#eb8f34;"> Installing Visual Paradigm on Ubuntu</h1>
        <h2 data-aos="fade-up">
            To install ArgoUML on Ubuntu follow the following steps:</h2> <br><br>
            <p><b>Step 1:</b> Open the Web browser and type/ paste the URL: ‘https://www.visual-paradigm.com/download/.’
        </p>
        <a href="sspics/vis1.png">
            <img src="sspics/vis1.png">
        </a><br><br>
        <p data-aos="fade-up">
            <b>step-2</b>  Click on the ‘Download Visual Paradigm’ button in red on the visual paradigm website.
        </p>    
        <a href="sspics/vis2.png">
            <img src="sspics/vis2.png"></a><br>
                 <a href="sspics/vis3.png">
            <img src="sspics/vis3.png"></a><br>
      <h2 data-aos="fade-up"> Update/Upgrade Package Repository

</h2>
        <p data-aos="fade-up">
<p data-aos="fade-up">3.Open the terminal and run the following command:
</p>
<div class="textContainer" data-aos="fade-up">
            <i id="commandText1">sudo apt update</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
            <button onclick="copyTextToClipboard('commandText1', this)">Copy</button>
        </div><br>
<p data-aos="fade-up">4. Enter your password and wait for the update to finish.
</p>
<p data-aos="fade-up">5. Next, run:
</p>
<div class="textContainer" data-aos="fade-up">
            <i id="commandText1">sudo apt upgrade</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
            <button onclick="copyTextToClipboard('commandText1', this)">Copy</button>
        </div><br>
          <a href="sspics/emua.jpeg">
            <img src="sspics/emua.jpeg"></a>
 <p data-aos="fade-up">Enter Y when prompted to continue with the upgrade and hit ENTER. Wait for the upgrade to finish.
</p>      
        
        <p data-aos="fade-up">After that keep this file in Desktop folder And then then enter.
        </p>
        <div class="textContainer" data-aos="fade-up">
            <i id="commandText2">cd Desktop</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
            <button onclick="copyTextToClipboard('commandText2', this)">Copy</button>
        </div><br>
        
        <a href="sspics/argo5.png">
            <img src="sspics/argo5.png"></a>
          <p data-aos="fade-up"> ). Extract the contents to a location of your choice. You can use the following command to extract .sh file:
        </p>
          <div class="textContainer" data-aos="fade-up">
            <i id="commandText2">sudo chmod 755 Visual_Paradigm_CE_16_3_20211131_Linux64.sh</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
            <button onclick="copyTextToClipboard('commandText2', this)">Copy</button>
        </div><br>
       
               <p data-aos="fade-up">Copy the below commad to open the application</p>
          <div class="textContainer" data-aos="fade-up">
            <i id="commandText2">./Visual_Paradigm_CE_16_3_20211131_Linux64.sh</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
            <button onclick="copyTextToClipboard('commandText2', this)">Copy</button>
        </div><br>
        <a href="sspics/vis4.png">
            <img src="sspics/vis4.png" style="width:600px;">
        </a>
       <p data-aos="fade-up">After successful installation it is showing like this.</p>
             <a href="sspics/vis5.png">
            <img src="sspics/vis5.png"style="width:600px;">
        </a>
              <p data-aos="fade-up"><b>Step 3:</b> Now, the installer will start running on the screen while showing the setup wizard on the user interface. Click ‘Next’ to view and read the license agreement provided by the software owner. To proceed with the installation, please read the license agreement carefully. Once you have reviewed the agreement, click on the option ‘I accept the agreement’ to indicate your acceptance.</p>
     <a href="sspics/vis6.png">
            <img src="sspics/vis6.png"style="width:600px;">
        </a>
          <p data-aos="fade-up"><b>Step 4:</b> Select the directory details for installing the application, and click ‘Next’. Create shortcuts when prompted with the options to do so, along with the preferred name, and then click ‘Next’.
 </p>
     <a href="sspics/vis7.png">
            <img src="sspics/vis7.png"style="width:600px;">
        </a>
        <p data-aos="fade-up"><b>Step 5:</b> After this, the File Association page opens. Here, check the ‘Visual Paradigm Project (*.vpp)’ to enable the system to open the application with a simple double-click action from the active mouse device. Then, click ‘Next’.
 </p>
     <a href="sspics/vis8.png">
            <img src="sspics/vis8.png"style="width:600px;">
        </a>
             <a href="sspics/vis9.png">
            <img src="sspics/vis9.png"style="width:600px;">
        </a>
             <p data-aos="fade-up"><b>Step 6:</b>  In the final installation page, the installer asks if you want to open the application after installation completion; click yes if required. Then, as a final step, click the ‘Finish’ button to complete the Visual Paradigm installation process.
 </p>
